events.name: Social Coding
events.description: A space for women coders to learn from each other, to practice and discuss learnings with fellow peers. This would be a weekly event of informal space to do coding. So bring your pet projects along or join one of our existing teams/ projects to work on. Featured Projects:https://trello.com/b/kl2BTwil/wwc-sg-social-coding-projects First timers, please read:Newbies Step-by-step Guide Please bring your own laptop. Agenda:6:30p - Choose your project and Start coding! ^_^8:30p - End session There will be pizza provided for this event, so please come and enjoy!  Also, we recommend to bring your own water bottle along. Psst, this event is intended for ladies only.
events.location: Palo-IT Innovation Studio, 56B Boat Quay (3rd Floor), Singapore
